
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 97/120 – Cache vs Persist

🎤 Interview Question

You have a DataFrame that is used multiple times in an ETL pipeline.

Write PySpark code to optimize the pipeline using caching.


---

✅ Recommended Solution

# Cache the DataFrame
df.cache()

# Trigger caching
df.count()

# Reuse multiple times
df.filter("salary > 50000").show()

df.groupBy("department").count().show()

df.select("name", "salary").show()

Using Persist

from pyspark import StorageLevel

df.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)

df.count()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Difference between cache() and persist()?

Answer

cache()	persist()

Uses MEMORY_AND_DISK (default in Spark)	User chooses storage level
Simple to use	More flexible



---

Q2. When should you use cache?

Answer

When the same DataFrame is reused multiple times in the pipeline.


---

Q3. When should you use persist?

Answer

When the DataFrame is too large to fit entirely in memory or when a different storage level is required.


